Halve the @bell pepper{1}, remove the core and seeds then thinly slice. Trim the @spring onion{1} then thinly slice.

Pop the @egg noodle nest{2} in a large #saucepan and cover with the boiling water. Put the pan on medium-high heat, bring back to the boil and cook the noodles for ~{4%minutes}. Drain in a #colander, submerge in cold water and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a #frying pan on high heat. Add the pepper, @mangetout{150%g} and half the spring onion. Stir-fry, until softened, ~{2%minutes}. Add the @king prawns{120} and stir-fry for another ~{2-3%minutes}.

Lower the heat slightly, add the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @chow mein paste{1} and @chow mein garnish{1} and the @water{50%ml}. Stir and simmer until the prawns are cooked through.

> The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the centre.

Drain the noodles again and add to the frying pan. Stir through until piping hot.

Serve the prawn chow mein in #bowls sprinkled with the remaining spring onion. Enjoy!